04980 /**
04981  * cvmx_uahc#_ohci0_hccommandstatus
04982  *
04983  * HCCOMMANDSTATUS = Host Controller Command Status Register
04984  *
04985  * The HcCommandStatus register is used by the Host Controller to receive commands issued by the Host Controller Driver, as well as reflecting the
04986  * current status of the Host Controller. To the Host Controller Driver, it appears to be a "write to set" register. The Host Controller must ensure
04987  * that bits written as '1' become set in the register while bits written as '0' remain unchanged in the register. The Host Controller Driver
04988  * may issue multiple distinct commands to the Host Controller without concern for corrupting previously issued commands. The Host Controller Driver
04989  * has normal read access to all bits.
04990  * The SchedulingOverrunCount field indicates the number of frames with which the Host Controller has detected the scheduling overrun error. This
04991  * occurs when the Periodic list does not complete before EOF. When a scheduling overrun error is detected, the Host Controller increments the counter
04992  * and sets the SchedulingOverrun field in the HcInterruptStatus register.
04993  */
04994 union cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccommandstatus {
04995     uint32_t u32;
04996     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccommandstatus_s {
04997 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
04998     uint32_t reserved_18_31               : 14;
04999     uint32_t soc                          : 2;  /**< SchedulingOverrunCount. These bits are incremented on each scheduling overrun
05000                                                          error. It is initialized to 00b and wraps around at 11b. This will be
05001                                                          incremented when a scheduling overrun is detected even if SchedulingOverrun
05002                                                          in HcInterruptStatus has already been set. This is used by HCD to monitor
05003                                                          any persistent scheduling problems. */
05004     uint32_t reserved_4_15                : 12;
05005     uint32_t ocr                          : 1;  /**< OwnershipChangeRequest. This bit is set by an OS HCD to request a change of
05006                                                          control of the HC. When set HC will set the OwnershipChange field in
05007                                                          HcInterruptStatus. After the changeover, this bit is cleared and remains so
05008                                                          until the next request from OS HCD. */
05009     uint32_t blf                          : 1;  /**< BulkListFilled This bit is used to indicate whether there are any TDs on the
05010                                                          Bulk list. It is set by HCD whenever it adds a TD to an ED in the Bulk list.
05011                                                          When HC begins to process the head of the Bulk list, it checks BF. As long
05012                                                          as BulkListFilled is 0, HC will not start processing the Bulk list. If
05013                                                          BulkListFilled is 1, HC will start processing the Bulk list and will set BF
05014                                                          to 0. If HC finds a TD on the list, then HC will set BulkListFilled to 1
05015                                                          causing the Bulk list processing to continue. If no TD is found on the Bulk
05016                                                          list,and if HCD does not set BulkListFilled, then BulkListFilled will still
05017                                                          be 0 when HC completes processing the Bulk list and Bulk list processing will
05018                                                          stop. */
05019     uint32_t clf                          : 1;  /**< ControlListFilled. This bit is used to indicate whether there are any TDs
05020                                                          on the Control list. It is set by HCD whenever it adds a TD to an ED in the
05021                                                          Control list. When HC begins to process the head of the Control list, it
05022                                                          checks CLF. As long as ControlListFilled is 0, HC will not start processing
05023                                                          the Control list. If CF is 1, HC will start processing the Control list and
05024                                                          will set ControlListFilled to 0. If HC finds a TD on the list, then HC will
05025                                                          set ControlListFilled to 1 causing the Control list processing to continue.
05026                                                          If no TD is found on the Control list, and if the HCD does not set
05027                                                          ControlListFilled, then ControlListFilled will still be 0 when HC completes
05028                                                          processing the Control list and Control list processing will stop. */
05029     uint32_t hcr                          : 1;  /**< HostControllerReset. This bit is set by HCD to initiate a software reset of
05030                                                          HC. Regardless of the functional state of HC, it moves to the USBSUSPEND
05031                                                          state in which most of the operational registers are reset except those
05032                                                          stated otherwise; e.g., the InterruptRouting field of HcControl, and no
05033                                                          Host bus accesses are allowed. This bit is cleared by HC upon the
05034                                                          completion of the reset operation. The reset operation must be completed
05035                                                          within 10 ms. This bit, when set, should not cause a reset to the Root Hub
05036                                                          and no subsequent reset signaling should be asserted to its downstream ports. */
05037 #else
05038     uint32_t hcr                          : 1;
05039     uint32_t clf                          : 1;
05040     uint32_t blf                          : 1;
05041     uint32_t ocr                          : 1;
05042     uint32_t reserved_4_15                : 12;
05043     uint32_t soc                          : 2;
05044     uint32_t reserved_18_31               : 14;
05045 #endif
05046     } s;
05047     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccommandstatus_s cn61xx;
05048     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccommandstatus_s cn63xx;
05049     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccommandstatus_s cn63xxp1;
05050     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccommandstatus_s cn66xx;
05051     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccommandstatus_s cn68xx;
05052     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccommandstatus_s cn68xxp1;
05053     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccommandstatus_s cnf71xx;
05054 };
05055 typedef union cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccommandstatus cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccommandstatus_t;
05056 
05057 /**
05058  * cvmx_uahc#_ohci0_hccontrol
05059  *
05060  * HCCONTROL = Host Controller Control Register
05061  *
05062  * The HcControl register defines the operating modes for the Host Controller. Most of the fields in this register are modified only by the Host Controller
05063  * Driver, except HostControllerFunctionalState and RemoteWakeupConnected.
05064  */
05065 union cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccontrol {
05066     uint32_t u32;
05067     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccontrol_s {
05068 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
05069     uint32_t reserved_11_31               : 21;
05070     uint32_t rwe                          : 1;  /**< RemoteWakeupEnable. This bit is used by HCD to enable or disable the remote wakeup
05071                                                          feature upon the detection of upstream resume signaling. When this bit is set and
05072                                                          the ResumeDetected bit in HcInterruptStatus is set, a remote wakeup is signaled
05073                                                          to the host system. Setting this bit has no impact on the generation of hardware
05074                                                          interrupt. */
05075     uint32_t rwc                          : 1;  /**< RemoteWakeupConnected.This bit indicates whether HC supports remote wakeup signaling.
05076                                                          If remote wakeup is supported and used by the system it is the responsibility of
05077                                                          system firmware to set this bit during POST. HC clears the bit upon a hardware reset
05078                                                          but does not alter it upon a software reset. Remote wakeup signaling of the host
05079                                                          system is host-bus-specific and is not described in this specification. */
05080     uint32_t ir                           : 1;  /**< InterruptRouting
05081                                                          This bit determines the routing of interrupts generated by events registered in
05082                                                          HcInterruptStatus. If clear, all interrupts are routed to the normal host bus
05083                                                          interrupt mechanism. If set, interrupts are routed to the System Management
05084                                                          Interrupt. HCD clears this bit upon a hardware reset, but it does not alter
05085                                                          this bit upon a software reset. HCD uses this bit as a tag to indicate the
05086                                                          ownership of HC. */
05087     uint32_t hcfs                         : 2;  /**< HostControllerFunctionalState for USB
05088                                                           00b: USBRESET
05089                                                           01b: USBRESUME
05090                                                           10b: USBOPERATIONAL
05091                                                           11b: USBSUSPEND
05092                                                          A transition to USBOPERATIONAL from another state causes SOF generation to begin
05093                                                          1 ms later. HCD may determine whether HC has begun sending SOFs by reading the
05094                                                          StartofFrame field of HcInterruptStatus.
05095                                                          This field may be changed by HC only when in the USBSUSPEND state. HC may move from
05096                                                          the USBSUSPEND state to the USBRESUME state after detecting the resume signaling
05097                                                          from a downstream port.
05098                                                          HC enters USBSUSPEND after a software reset, whereas it enters USBRESET after a
05099                                                          hardware reset. The latter also resets the Root Hub and asserts subsequent reset
05100                                                          signaling to downstream ports. */
05101     uint32_t ble                          : 1;  /**< BulkListEnable. This bit is set to enable the processing of the Bulk list in the
05102                                                          next Frame. If cleared by HCD, processing of the Bulk list does not occur after
05103                                                          the next SOF. HC checks this bit whenever it determines to process the list. When
05104                                                          disabled, HCD may modify the list. If HcBulkCurrentED is pointing to an ED to be
05105                                                          removed, HCD must advance the pointer by updating HcBulkCurrentED before re-enabling
05106                                                          processing of the list. */
05107     uint32_t cle                          : 1;  /**< ControlListEnable. This bit is set to enable the processing of the Control list in
05108                                                          the next Frame. If cleared by HCD, processing of the Control list does not occur
05109                                                          after the next SOF. HC must check this bit whenever it determines to process the
05110                                                          list. When disabled, HCD may modify the list. If HcControlCurrentED is pointing to
05111                                                          an ED to be removed, HCD must advance the pointer by updating HcControlCurrentED
05112                                                          before re-enabling processing of the list. */
05113     uint32_t ie                           : 1;  /**< IsochronousEnable This bit is used by HCD to enable/disable processing of
05114                                                          isochronous EDs. While processing the periodic list in a Frame, HC checks the
05115                                                          status of this bit when it finds an Isochronous ED (F=1). If set (enabled), HC
05116                                                          continues processing the EDs. If cleared (disabled), HC halts processing of the
05117                                                          periodic list (which now contains only isochronous EDs) and begins processing the
05118                                                          Bulk/Control lists. Setting this bit is guaranteed to take effect in the next
05119                                                          Frame (not the current Frame). */
05120     uint32_t ple                          : 1;  /**< PeriodicListEnable. This bit is set to enable the processing of the periodic list
05121                                                          in the next Frame. If cleared by HCD, processing of the periodic list does not
05122                                                          occur after the next SOF. HC must check this bit before it starts processing
05123                                                          the list. */
05124     uint32_t cbsr                         : 2;  /**< ControlBulkServiceRatio. This specifies the service ratio between Control and
05125                                                          Bulk EDs. Before processing any of the nonperiodic lists, HC must compare the
05126                                                          ratio specified with its internal count on how many nonempty Control EDs have
05127                                                          been processed, in determining whether to continue serving another Control ED
05128                                                          or switching to Bulk EDs. The internal count will be retained when crossing
05129                                                          the frame boundary. In case of reset, HCD is responsible for restoring this
05130                                                          value.
05131 
05132                                                            CBSR   No. of Control EDs Over Bulk EDs Served
05133                                                             0             1:1
05134                                                             1             2:1
05135                                                             2             3:1
05136                                                             3             4:1 */
05137 #else
05138     uint32_t cbsr                         : 2;
05139     uint32_t ple                          : 1;
05140     uint32_t ie                           : 1;
05141     uint32_t cle                          : 1;
05142     uint32_t ble                          : 1;
05143     uint32_t hcfs                         : 2;
05144     uint32_t ir                           : 1;
05145     uint32_t rwc                          : 1;
05146     uint32_t rwe                          : 1;
05147     uint32_t reserved_11_31               : 21;
05148 #endif
05149     } s;
05150     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccontrol_s   cn61xx;
05151     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccontrol_s   cn63xx;
05152     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccontrol_s   cn63xxp1;
05153     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccontrol_s   cn66xx;
05154     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccontrol_s   cn68xx;
05155     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccontrol_s   cn68xxp1;
05156     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccontrol_s   cnf71xx;
05157 };
05158 typedef union cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccontrol cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccontrol_t;

05160 /**
05161  * cvmx_uahc#_ohci0_hccontrolcurrented
05162  *
05163  * HCCONTROLCURRENTED = Host Controller Control Current ED Register
05164  *
05165  * The HcControlCurrentED register contains the physical address of the current Endpoint Descriptor of the Control list.
05166  */
05167 union cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccontrolcurrented {
05168     uint32_t u32;
05169     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccontrolcurrented_s {
05170 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
05171     uint32_t cced                         : 28; /**< ControlCurrentED. This pointer is advanced to the next ED after serving the
05172                                                          present one. HC will continue processing the list from where it left off in
05173                                                          the last Frame. When it reaches the end of the Control list, HC checks the
05174                                                          ControlListFilled of in HcCommandStatus. If set, it copies the content of
05175                                                          HcControlHeadED to HcControlCurrentED and clears the bit. If not set, it
05176                                                          does nothing. HCD is allowed to modify this register only when the
05177                                                          ControlListEnable of HcControl is cleared. When set, HCD only reads the
05178                                                          instantaneous value of this register. Initially, this is set to zero to
05179                                                          indicate the end of the Control list. */
05180     uint32_t reserved_0_3                 : 4;
05181 #else
05182     uint32_t reserved_0_3                 : 4;
05183     uint32_t cced                         : 28;
05184 #endif
05185     } s;
05186     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccontrolcurrented_s cn61xx;
05187     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccontrolcurrented_s cn63xx;
05188     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccontrolcurrented_s cn63xxp1;
05189     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hccontrolcurrented_s cn66xx;

05260  * HCFMINTERVAL = Host Controller Frame Interval Register
05261  *
05262  * The HcFmInterval register contains a 14-bit value which indicates the bit time interval in a Frame, (i.e., between two consecutive SOFs), and a 15-bit value
05263  * indicating the Full Speed maximum packet size that the Host Controller may transmit or receive without causing scheduling overrun. The Host Controller Driver
05264  * may carry out minor adjustment on the FrameInterval by writing a new value over the present one at each SOF. This provides the programmability necessary for
05265  * the Host Controller to synchronize with an external clocking resource and to adjust any unknown local clock offset.
05266  */

05272                                                          FrameInterval. */

05274                                                          Largest Data Packet Counter at the beginning of each frame. The counter value
05275                                                          represents the largest amount of data in bits which can be sent or received by
05276                                                          the HC in a single transaction at any given time without causing scheduling
05277                                                          overrun. The field value is calculated by the HCD. */
05278     uint32_t reserved_14_15               : 2;

05281                                                          value of this field before resetting HC. By setting the HostControllerReset
05282                                                          field of HcCommandStatus as this will cause the HC to reset this field to its
05283                                                          nominal value. HCD may choose to restore the stored value upon the completion
05284                                                          of the Reset sequence. */
05285 #else

05376  *
05377  * The HcHCCA register contains the physical address of the Host Controller Communication Area. The Host Controller Driver determines the alignment restrictions

05380  * is used to hold the control structures and the Interrupt table that are accessed by both the Host Controller and the Host Controller Driver.

05390     uint32_t hcca                         : 24;
05391 #endif

05408  * Each disable bit in the HcInterruptDisable register corresponds to an associated interrupt bit in the HcInterruptStatus register. The HcInterruptDisable

05418                                                          A '1' written to this field disables interrupt generation due to events
05419                                                          specified in the other bits of this register. This field is set after a
05420                                                          hardware or software reset. */

05425     uint32_t ue                           : 1;  /**< 0 - Ignore; 1 - Disable interrupt generation due to Unrecoverable Error. */
05426     uint32_t rd                           : 1;  /**< 0 - Ignore; 1 - Disable interrupt generation due to Resume Detect. */

05428     uint32_t wdh                          : 1;  /**< 0 - Ignore; 1 - Disable interrupt generation due to HcDoneHead Writeback. */
05429     uint32_t so                           : 1;  /**< 0 - Ignore; 1 - Disable interrupt generation due to Scheduling Overrun. */
05430 #else
05431     uint32_t so                           : 1;
05432     uint32_t wdh                          : 1;
05433     uint32_t sf                           : 1;
05434     uint32_t rd                           : 1;
05435     uint32_t ue                           : 1;
05436     uint32_t fno                          : 1;
05437     uint32_t rhsc                         : 1;
05438     uint32_t reserved_7_29                : 23;
05439     uint32_t oc                           : 1;
05440     uint32_t mie                          : 1;
05441 #endif
05442     } s;

05453 /**
05454  * cvmx_uahc#_ohci0_hcinterruptenable
05455  *
05456  * HCINTERRUPTENABLE = Host Controller InterruptEnable Register
05457  *
05458  * Each enable bit in the HcInterruptEnable register corresponds to an associated interrupt bit in the HcInterruptStatus register. The HcInterruptEnable
05459  * register is used to control which events generate a hardware interrupt. When a bit is set in the HcInterruptStatus register AND the corresponding bit
05460  * in the HcInterruptEnable register is set AND the MasterInterruptEnable bit is set, then a hardware interrupt is requested on the host bus.
05461  * Writing a '1' to a bit in this register sets the corresponding bit, whereas writing a '0' to a bit in this register leaves the corresponding bit
05462  * unchanged. On read, the current value of this register is returned.

05464 union cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcinterruptenable {

05469                                                          A '1' written to this field enables interrupt generation due to events
05470                                                          specified in the other bits of this register. This is used by HCD as a Master
05471                                                          Interrupt Enable. */
05472     uint32_t oc                           : 1;  /**< 0 - Ignore; 1 - Enable interrupt generation due to Ownership Change. */
05473     uint32_t reserved_7_29                : 23;

05475     uint32_t fno                          : 1;  /**< 0 - Ignore; 1 - Enable interrupt generation due to Frame Number Overflow. */

05477     uint32_t rd                           : 1;  /**< 0 - Ignore; 1 - Enable interrupt generation due to Resume Detect. */
05478     uint32_t sf                           : 1;  /**< 0 - Ignore; 1 - Enable interrupt generation due to Start of Frame. */
05479     uint32_t wdh                          : 1;  /**< 0 - Ignore; 1 - Enable interrupt generation due to HcDoneHead Writeback. */
05480     uint32_t so                           : 1;  /**< 0 - Ignore; 1 - Enable interrupt generation due to Scheduling Overrun. */
05481 #else
05482     uint32_t so                           : 1;
05483     uint32_t wdh                          : 1;
05484     uint32_t sf                           : 1;
05485     uint32_t rd                           : 1;
05486     uint32_t ue                           : 1;
05487     uint32_t fno                          : 1;
05488     uint32_t rhsc                         : 1;
05489     uint32_t reserved_7_29                : 23;
05490     uint32_t oc                           : 1;
05491     uint32_t mie                          : 1;
05492 #endif

05504 /**
05505  * cvmx_uahc#_ohci0_hcinterruptstatus
05506  *
05507  * HCINTERRUPTSTATUS = Host Controller InterruptStatus Register
05508  *
05509  * This register provides status on various events that cause hardware interrupts. When an event occurs, Host Controller sets the corresponding bit
05510  * in this register. When a bit becomes set, a hardware interrupt is generated if the interrupt is enabled in the HcInterruptEnable register
05511  * and the MasterInterruptEnable bit is set. The Host Controller Driver may clear specific bits in this register by writing '1' to bit positions
05512  * to be cleared. The Host Controller Driver may not set any of these bits. The Host Controller will never clear the bit.
05513  */
05514 union cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcinterruptstatus {
05515     uint32_t u32;
05516     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcinterruptstatus_s {
05517 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
05518     uint32_t reserved_31_31               : 1;
05519     uint32_t oc                           : 1;  /**< OwnershipChange. This bit is set by HC when HCD sets the OwnershipChangeRequest
05520                                                          field in HcCommandStatus. This event, when unmasked, will always generate an
05521                                                          System Management Interrupt (SMI) immediately. This bit is tied to 0b when the
05522                                                          SMI pin is not implemented. */
05523     uint32_t reserved_7_29                : 23;
05524     uint32_t rhsc                         : 1;  /**< RootHubStatusChange. This bit is set when the content of HcRhStatus or the
05525                                                          content of any of HcRhPortStatus[NumberofDownstreamPort] has changed. */
05526     uint32_t fno                          : 1;  /**< FrameNumberOverflow. This bit is set when the MSb of HcFmNumber (bit 15)
05527                                                          changes value, from 0 to 1 or from 1 to 0, and after HccaFrameNumber has been
05528                                                          updated. */
05529     uint32_t ue                           : 1;  /**< UnrecoverableError. This bit is set when HC detects a system error not related
05530                                                          to USB. HC should not proceed with any processing nor signaling before the
05531                                                          system error has been corrected. HCD clears this bit after HC has been reset. */
05532     uint32_t rd                           : 1;  /**< ResumeDetected. This bit is set when HC detects that a device on the USB is
05533                                                           asserting resume signaling. It is the transition from no resume signaling to
05534                                                          resume signaling causing this bit to be set. This bit is not set when HCD
05535                                                          sets the USBRESUME state. */
05536     uint32_t sf                           : 1;  /**< StartofFrame. This bit is set by HC at each start of a frame and after the
05537                                                          update of HccaFrameNumber. HC also generates a SOF token at the same time. */
05538     uint32_t wdh                          : 1;  /**< WritebackDoneHead. This bit is set immediately after HC has written
05539                                                          HcDoneHead to HccaDoneHead. Further updates of the HccaDoneHead will not
05540                                                          occur until this bit has been cleared. HCD should only clear this bit after
05541                                                          it has saved the content of HccaDoneHead. */
05542     uint32_t so                           : 1;  /**< SchedulingOverrun. This bit is set when the USB schedule for the current
05543                                                          Frame overruns and after the update of HccaFrameNumber. A scheduling overrun
05544                                                          will also cause the SchedulingOverrunCount of HcCommandStatus to be
05545                                                          incremented. */
05546 #else
05547     uint32_t so                           : 1;
05548     uint32_t wdh                          : 1;
05549     uint32_t sf                           : 1;
05550     uint32_t rd                           : 1;
05551     uint32_t ue                           : 1;
05552     uint32_t fno                          : 1;
05553     uint32_t rhsc                         : 1;
05554     uint32_t reserved_7_29                : 23;
05555     uint32_t oc                           : 1;
05556     uint32_t reserved_31_31               : 1;
05557 #endif
05558     } s;
05559     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcinterruptstatus_s cn61xx;
05560     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcinterruptstatus_s cn63xx;
05561     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcinterruptstatus_s cn63xxp1;
05562     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcinterruptstatus_s cn66xx;
05563     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcinterruptstatus_s cn68xx;
05564     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcinterruptstatus_s cn68xxp1;
05565     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcinterruptstatus_s cnf71xx;

05569 /**
05570  * cvmx_uahc#_ohci0_hclsthreshold
05571  *
05572  * HCLSTHRESHOLD = Host Controller LS Threshold Register
05573  *
05574  * The HcLSThreshold register contains an 11-bit value used by the Host Controller to determine whether to commit to the transfer of a maximum of 8-byte
05575  * LS packet before EOF. Neither the Host Controller nor the Host Controller Driver are allowed to change this value.
05576  */
05577 union cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hclsthreshold {
05578     uint32_t u32;

05585                                                          if FrameRemaining >= this field. The value is calculated by HCD

05598     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hclsthreshold_s cnf71xx;

05698 /**
05699  * cvmx_uahc#_ohci0_hcrhdescriptora
05700  *
05701  * HCRHDESCRIPTORA = Host Controller Root Hub DescriptorA Register
05702  *
05703  * The HcRhDescriptorA register is the first register of two describing the characteristics of the Root Hub. Reset values are implementation-specific.
05704  * The descriptor length (11), descriptor type (0x29), and hub controller current (0) fields of the hub Class Descriptor are emulated by the HCD. All
05705  * other fields are located in the HcRhDescriptorA and HcRhDescriptorB registers.
05706  */
05707 union cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhdescriptora {
05708     uint32_t u32;
05709     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhdescriptora_s {
05710 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
05711     uint32_t potpgt                       : 8;  /**< PowerOnToPowerGoodTime. This byte specifies the duration HCD has to wait before
05712                                                          accessing a powered-on port of the Root Hub. It is implementation-specific. The
05713                                                          unit of time is 2 ms. The duration is calculated as POTPGT * 2 ms. */
05714     uint32_t reserved_13_23               : 11;
05715     uint32_t nocp                         : 1;  /**< NoOverCurrentProtection. This bit describes how the overcurrent status for the
05716                                                          Root Hub ports are reported. When this bit is cleared, the
05717                                                          OverCurrentProtectionMode field specifies global or per-port reporting.
05718                                                          - 0: Over-current status is reported  collectively for all downstream ports
05719                                                          - 1: No overcurrent protection supported */
05720     uint32_t ocpm                         : 1;  /**< OverCurrentProtectionMode. This bit describes how the overcurrent status for
05721                                                          the Root Hub ports are reported. At reset, this fields should reflect the same
05722                                                          mode as PowerSwitchingMode. This field is valid only if the
05723                                                          NoOverCurrentProtection field is cleared. 0: over-current status is reported
05724                                                          collectively for all downstream ports 1: over-current status is reported on a
05725                                                          per-port basis */
05726     uint32_t dt                           : 1;  /**< DeviceType. This bit specifies that the Root Hub is not a compound device. The
05727                                                          Root Hub is not permitted to be a compound device. This field should always
05728                                                          read/write 0. */
05729     uint32_t psm                          : 1;  /**< PowerSwitchingMode. This bit is used to specify how the power switching of
05730                                                          the Root Hub ports is controlled. It is implementation-specific. This field
05731                                                          is only valid if the NoPowerSwitching field is cleared. 0: all ports are
05732                                                          powered at the same time. 1: each port is powered individually.  This mode
05733                                                          allows port power to be controlled by either the global switch or per-port
05734                                                          switching. If the PortPowerControlMask bit is set, the port responds only
05735                                                          to port power commands (Set/ClearPortPower). If the port mask is cleared,
05736                                                          then the port is controlled only by the global power switch
05737                                                          (Set/ClearGlobalPower). */
05738     uint32_t nps                          : 1;  /**< NoPowerSwitching These bits are used to specify whether power switching is
05739                                                          supported or port are always powered. It is implementation-specific. When
05740                                                          this bit is cleared, the PowerSwitchingMode specifies global or per-port
05741                                                          switching.
05742                                                           - 0: Ports are power switched
05743                                                           - 1: Ports are always powered on when the HC is powered on */
05744     uint32_t ndp                          : 8;  /**< NumberDownstreamPorts. These bits specify the number of downstream ports
05745                                                          supported by the Root Hub. It is implementation-specific. The minimum number
05746                                                          of ports is 1. The maximum number of ports supported by OpenHCI is 15. */
05747 #else
05748     uint32_t ndp                          : 8;
05749     uint32_t nps                          : 1;
05750     uint32_t psm                          : 1;
05751     uint32_t dt                           : 1;
05752     uint32_t ocpm                         : 1;
05753     uint32_t nocp                         : 1;
05754     uint32_t reserved_13_23               : 11;
05755     uint32_t potpgt                       : 8;
05756 #endif
05757     } s;
05758     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhdescriptora_s cn61xx;
05759     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhdescriptora_s cn63xx;
05760     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhdescriptora_s cn63xxp1;
05761     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhdescriptora_s cn66xx;
05762     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhdescriptora_s cn68xx;
05763     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhdescriptora_s cn68xxp1;
05764     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhdescriptora_s cnf71xx;
05765 };
05766 typedef union cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhdescriptora cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhdescriptora_t;

05768 /**
05769  * cvmx_uahc#_ohci0_hcrhdescriptorb
05770  *
05771  * HCRHDESCRIPTORB = Host Controller Root Hub DescriptorB Register
05772  *
05773  * The HcRhDescriptorB register is the second register of two describing the characteristics of the Root Hub. These fields are written during
05774  * initialization to correspond with the system implementation. Reset values are implementation-specific.
05775  */
05776 union cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhdescriptorb {
05777     uint32_t u32;
05778     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhdescriptorb_s {
05779 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
05780     uint32_t ppcm                         : 16; /**< PortPowerControlMask.
05781                                                          Each bit indicates if a port is affected by a global power control command
05782                                                          when PowerSwitchingMode is set. When set, the port's power state is only
05783                                                          affected by per-port power control (Set/ClearPortPower). When cleared, the
05784                                                          port is controlled by the global power switch (Set/ClearGlobalPower). If
05785                                                          the device is configured to global switching mode (PowerSwitchingMode=0),
05786                                                          this field is not valid.
05787                                                             bit 0: Reserved
05788                                                             bit 1: Ganged-power mask on Port \#1
05789                                                             bit 2: Ganged-power mask on Port \#2
05790                                                             - ...
05791                                                             bit15: Ganged-power mask on Port \#15 */
05792     uint32_t dr                           : 16; /**< DeviceRemovable.
05793                                                          Each bit is dedicated to a port of the Root Hub. When cleared,the attached
05794                                                          device is removable. When set, the attached device is not removable.
05795                                                              bit 0: Reserved
05796                                                              bit 1: Device attached to Port \#1
05797                                                              bit 2: Device attached to Port \#2
05798                                                              - ...
05799                                                              bit15: Device attached to Port \#15 */
05800 #else
05801     uint32_t dr                           : 16;
05802     uint32_t ppcm                         : 16;
05803 #endif
05804     } s;
05805     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhdescriptorb_s cn61xx;
05806     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhdescriptorb_s cn63xx;
05807     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhdescriptorb_s cn63xxp1;
05808     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhdescriptorb_s cn66xx;
05809     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhdescriptorb_s cn68xx;
05810     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhdescriptorb_s cn68xxp1;
05811     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhdescriptorb_s cnf71xx;
05812 };

05814 
05815 /**
05816  * cvmx_uahc#_ohci0_hcrhportstatus#
05817  *
05818  * HCRHPORTSTATUSX = Host Controller Root Hub Port X Status Registers
05819  *
05820  * The HcRhPortStatus[1:NDP] register is used to control and report port events on a per-port basis. NumberDownstreamPorts represents the number
05821  * of HcRhPortStatus registers that are implemented in hardware. The lower word is used to reflect the port status, whereas the upper word reflects
05822  * the status change bits. Some status bits are implemented with special write behavior (see below). If a transaction (token through handshake) is
05823  * in progress when a write to change port status occurs, the resulting port status change must be postponed until the transaction completes.
05824  * Reserved bits should always be written '0'.
05825  */
05826 union cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhportstatusx {
05827     uint32_t u32;
05828     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhportstatusx_s {
05829 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
05830     uint32_t reserved_21_31               : 11;
05831     uint32_t prsc                         : 1;  /**< PortResetStatusChange. This bit is set at the end of the 10-ms port reset
05832                                                          signal. The HCD writes a '1' to clear this bit. Writing a '0' has no effect.
05833                                                             0 = port reset is not complete
05834                                                             1 = port reset is complete */
05835     uint32_t ocic                         : 1;  /**< PortOverCurrentIndicatorChange. This bit is valid only if overcurrent
05836                                                          conditions are reported on a per-port basis. This bit is set when Root Hub
05837                                                          changes the PortOverCurrentIndicator bit. The HCD writes a '1' to clear this
05838                                                          bit. Writing a  '0'  has no effect.
05839                                                             0 = no change in PortOverCurrentIndicator
05840                                                             1 = PortOverCurrentIndicator has changed */
05841     uint32_t pssc                         : 1;  /**< PortSuspendStatusChange. This bit is set when the full resume sequence has
05842                                                          been completed. This sequence includes the 20-s resume pulse, LS EOP, and
05843                                                          3-ms resychronization delay.
05844                                                          The HCD writes a '1' to clear this bit. Writing a '0' has no effect. This
05845                                                          bit is also cleared when ResetStatusChange is set.
05846                                                             0 = resume is not completed
05847                                                             1 = resume completed */
05848     uint32_t pesc                         : 1;  /**< PortEnableStatusChange. This bit is set when hardware events cause the
05849                                                          PortEnableStatus bit to be cleared. Changes from HCD writes do not set this
05850                                                          bit. The HCD writes a '1' to clear this bit. Writing a '0' has no effect.
05851                                                            0 = no change in PortEnableStatus
05852                                                            1 = change in PortEnableStatus */
05853     uint32_t csc                          : 1;  /**< ConnectStatusChange. This bit is set whenever a connect or disconnect event
05854                                                          occurs. The HCD writes a '1' to clear this bit. Writing a '0' has no
05855                                                          effect. If CurrentConnectStatus is cleared when a SetPortReset,SetPortEnable,
05856                                                          or SetPortSuspend write occurs, this bit is set to force the driver to
05857                                                          re-evaluate the connection status since these writes should not occur if the
05858                                                          port is disconnected.
05859                                                            0 = no change in CurrentConnectStatus
05860                                                            1 = change in CurrentConnectStatus
05861                                                          Note: If the DeviceRemovable[NDP] bit is set, this bit is set only after a
05862                                                           Root Hub reset to inform the system that the device is attached. Description */
05863     uint32_t reserved_10_15               : 6;
05864     uint32_t lsda                         : 1;  /**< (read) LowSpeedDeviceAttached. This bit indicates the speed of the device
05865                                                               attached to this port. When set, a Low Speed device is attached to this
05866                                                               port. When clear, a Full Speed device is attached to this port. This
05867                                                               field is valid only when the CurrentConnectStatus is set.
05868                                                                  0 = full speed device attached
05869                                                                  1 = low speed device attached
05870                                                          (write) ClearPortPower. The HCD clears the PortPowerStatus bit by writing a
05871                                                               '1' to this bit. Writing a '0' has no effect. */
05872     uint32_t pps                          : 1;  /**< (read) PortPowerStatus. This bit reflects the port's power status, regardless
05873                                                              of the type of power switching implemented. This bit is cleared if an
05874                                                              overcurrent condition is detected. HCD sets this bit by writing
05875                                                              SetPortPower or SetGlobalPower. HCD clears this bit by writing
05876                                                              ClearPortPower or ClearGlobalPower. Which power control switches are
05877                                                              enabled is determined by PowerSwitchingMode and PortPortControlMask[NDP].
05878                                                              In global switching mode (PowerSwitchingMode=0), only Set/ClearGlobalPower
05879                                                                controls this bit. In per-port power switching (PowerSwitchingMode=1),
05880                                                                if the PortPowerControlMask[NDP] bit for the port is set, only
05881                                                                Set/ClearPortPower commands are enabled. If the mask is not set, only
05882                                                                Set/ClearGlobalPower commands are enabled. When port power is disabled,
05883                                                                CurrentConnectStatus, PortEnableStatus, PortSuspendStatus, and
05884                                                                PortResetStatus should be reset.
05885                                                                   0 = port power is off
05886                                                                   1 = port power is on
05887                                                          (write) SetPortPower. The HCD writes a '1' to set the PortPowerStatus bit.
05888                                                                Writing a '0' has no effect. Note: This bit is always reads '1'
05889                                                                if power switching is not supported. */
05890     uint32_t reserved_5_7                 : 3;
05891     uint32_t prs                          : 1;  /**< (read) PortResetStatus. When this bit is set by a write to SetPortReset, port
05892                                                                reset signaling is asserted. When reset is completed, this bit is
05893                                                                cleared when PortResetStatusChange is set. This bit cannot be set if
05894                                                                CurrentConnectStatus is cleared.
05895                                                                   0 = port reset signal is not active
05896                                                                1 = port reset signal is active
05897                                                          (write) SetPortReset. The HCD sets the port reset signaling by writing a '1'
05898                                                                to this bit. Writing a '0'has no effect. If CurrentConnectStatus is
05899                                                                cleared, this write does not set PortResetStatus, but instead sets
05900                                                                ConnectStatusChange. This informs the driver that it attempted to reset
05901                                                                a disconnected port. Description */
05902     uint32_t poci                         : 1;  /**< (read) PortOverCurrentIndicator. This bit is only valid when the Root Hub is
05903                                                                 configured in such a way that overcurrent conditions are reported on a
05904                                                                 per-port basis. If per-port overcurrent reporting is not supported, this
05905                                                                 bit is set to 0. If cleared, all power operations are normal for this
05906                                                                 port. If set, an overcurrent condition exists on this port. This bit
05907                                                                 always reflects the overcurrent input signal
05908                                                                   0 = no overcurrent condition.
05909                                                                   1 = overcurrent condition detected.
05910                                                          (write) ClearSuspendStatus. The HCD writes a '1' to initiate a resume.
05911                                                                  Writing  a '0' has no effect. A resume is initiated only if
05912                                                                  PortSuspendStatus is set. */
05913     uint32_t pss                          : 1;  /**< (read) PortSuspendStatus. This bit indicates the port is suspended or in the
05914                                                               resume sequence. It is set by a SetSuspendState write and cleared when
05915                                                               PortSuspendStatusChange is set at the end of the resume interval. This
05916                                                               bit cannot be set if CurrentConnectStatus is cleared. This bit is also
05917                                                               cleared when PortResetStatusChange is set at the end of the port reset
05918                                                               or when the HC is placed in the USBRESUME state. If an upstream resume is
05919                                                               in progress, it should propagate to the HC.
05920                                                                  0 = port is not suspended
05921                                                                  1 = port is suspended
05922                                                          (write) SetPortSuspend. The HCD sets the PortSuspendStatus bit by writing a
05923                                                               '1' to this bit. Writing a '0' has no effect. If CurrentConnectStatus
05924                                                                 is cleared, this write does not set PortSuspendStatus; instead it sets
05925                                                                 ConnectStatusChange.This informs the driver that it attempted to suspend
05926                                                                 a disconnected port. */
05927     uint32_t pes                          : 1;  /**< (read) PortEnableStatus. This bit indicates whether the port is enabled or
05928                                                               disabled. The Root Hub may clear this bit when an overcurrent condition,
05929                                                               disconnect event, switched-off power, or operational bus error such
05930                                                               as babble is detected. This change also causes PortEnabledStatusChange
05931                                                               to be set. HCD sets this bit by writing SetPortEnable and clears it by
05932                                                               writing ClearPortEnable. This bit cannot be set when CurrentConnectStatus
05933                                                               is cleared. This bit is also set, if not already, at the completion of a
05934                                                               port reset when ResetStatusChange is set or port suspend when
05935                                                               SuspendStatusChange is set.
05936                                                                 0 = port is disabled
05937                                                                 1 = port is enabled
05938                                                          (write) SetPortEnable. The HCD sets PortEnableStatus by writing a '1'.
05939                                                               Writing a '0' has no effect. If CurrentConnectStatus is cleared, this
05940                                                               write does not set PortEnableStatus, but instead sets ConnectStatusChange.
05941                                                               This informs the driver that it attempted to enable a disconnected port. */
05942     uint32_t ccs                          : 1;  /**< (read) CurrentConnectStatus. This bit reflects the current state of the
05943                                                                downstream port.
05944                                                                  0 = no device connected
05945                                                                  1 = device connected
05946                                                          (write) ClearPortEnable.
05947                                                                 The HCD writes a '1' to this bit to clear the PortEnableStatus bit.
05948                                                                 Writing a '0' has no effect. The CurrentConnectStatus is not
05949                                                                 affected by any write.
05950                                                           Note: This bit is always read '1b' when the attached device is
05951                                                                 nonremovable (DeviceRemoveable[NDP]). */
05952 #else
05953     uint32_t ccs                          : 1;
05954     uint32_t pes                          : 1;
05955     uint32_t pss                          : 1;
05956     uint32_t poci                         : 1;
05957     uint32_t prs                          : 1;
05958     uint32_t reserved_5_7                 : 3;
05959     uint32_t pps                          : 1;
05960     uint32_t lsda                         : 1;
05961     uint32_t reserved_10_15               : 6;
05962     uint32_t csc                          : 1;
05963     uint32_t pesc                         : 1;
05964     uint32_t pssc                         : 1;
05965     uint32_t ocic                         : 1;
05966     uint32_t prsc                         : 1;
05967     uint32_t reserved_21_31               : 11;
05968 #endif
05969     } s;
05970     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhportstatusx_s cn61xx;
05971     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhportstatusx_s cn63xx;
05972     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhportstatusx_s cn63xxp1;
05973     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhportstatusx_s cn66xx;
05974     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhportstatusx_s cn68xx;
05975     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhportstatusx_s cn68xxp1;
05976     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhportstatusx_s cnf71xx;
05977 };
05978 typedef union cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhportstatusx cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhportstatusx_t;

05980 /**
05981  * cvmx_uahc#_ohci0_hcrhstatus
05982  *
05983  * HCRHSTATUS = Host Controller Root Hub Status Register
05984  *
05985  * The HcRhStatus register is divided into two parts. The lower word of a Dword represents the Hub Status field and the upper word represents the Hub
05986  * Status Change field. Reserved bits should always be written '0'.
05987  */
05988 union cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhstatus {
05989     uint32_t u32;
05990     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhstatus_s {
05991 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
05992     uint32_t crwe                         : 1;  /**< (write) ClearRemoteWakeupEnable Writing a '1' clears DeviceRemoveWakeupEnable.
05993                                                          Writing a '0' has no effect. */
05994     uint32_t reserved_18_30               : 13;
05995     uint32_t ccic                         : 1;  /**< OverCurrentIndicatorChange. This bit is set by hardware when a change has
05996                                                          occurred to the OCI field of this register. The HCD clears this bit by
05997                                                          writing a '1'. Writing a '0' has no effect. */
05998     uint32_t lpsc                         : 1;  /**< (read) LocalPowerStatusChange. The Root Hub does not support the local power
05999                                                                 status feature; thus, this bit is always read as '0'.
06000                                                          (write) SetGlobalPower In global power mode (PowerSwitchingMode=0), This bit
06001                                                                  is written to '1' to turn on power to all ports (clear PortPowerStatus).
06002                                                                  In per-port power mode, it sets PortPowerStatus only on ports whose
06003                                                                  PortPowerControlMask bit is not set. Writing a '0' has no effect. */
06004     uint32_t drwe                         : 1;  /**< (read) DeviceRemoteWakeupEnable. This bit enables a ConnectStatusChange bit as
06005                                                                 a resume event, causing a USBSUSPEND to USBRESUME state transition and
06006                                                                 setting the ResumeDetected interrupt. 0 = ConnectStatusChange is not a
06007                                                                 remote wakeup event. 1 = ConnectStatusChange is a remote wakeup event.
06008                                                          (write) SetRemoteWakeupEnable Writing a '1' sets DeviceRemoveWakeupEnable.
06009                                                                  Writing a '0' has no effect. */
06010     uint32_t reserved_2_14                : 13;
06011     uint32_t oci                          : 1;  /**< OverCurrentIndicator. This bit reports overcurrent conditions when the global
06012                                                          reporting is implemented. When set, an overcurrent condition exists. When
06013                                                          cleared, all power operations are normal. If per-port overcurrent protection
06014                                                          is implemented this bit is always '0' */
06015     uint32_t lps                          : 1;  /**< (read)  LocalPowerStatus. The Root Hub does not support the local power status
06016                                                                  feature; thus, this bit is always read as '0.
06017                                                          (write) ClearGlobalPower. In global power mode (PowerSwitchingMode=0), This
06018                                                                  bit is written to '1' to turn off power to all ports
06019                                                                  (clear PortPowerStatus). In per-port power mode, it clears
06020                                                                  PortPowerStatus only on ports whose PortPowerControlMask bit is not
06021                                                                  set. Writing a '0' has no effect. Description */
06022 #else
06023     uint32_t lps                          : 1;
06024     uint32_t oci                          : 1;
06025     uint32_t reserved_2_14                : 13;
06026     uint32_t drwe                         : 1;
06027     uint32_t lpsc                         : 1;
06028     uint32_t ccic                         : 1;
06029     uint32_t reserved_18_30               : 13;
06030     uint32_t crwe                         : 1;
06031 #endif
06032     } s;
06033     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhstatus_s  cn61xx;
06034     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhstatus_s  cn63xx;
06035     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhstatus_s  cn63xxp1;
06036     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhstatus_s  cn66xx;
06037     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhstatus_s  cn68xx;
06038     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhstatus_s  cn68xxp1;
06039     struct cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhstatus_s  cnf71xx;
06040 };
06041 typedef union cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhstatus cvmx_uahcx_ohci0_hcrhstatus_t;
